text.tspan: Abby was the daughter of the people who lived here
before your now-deceased relative did. She was shy,
but kind of reckless in life. This caused her to like to
do things that made her parents worried, such as
playing with fire and eating things off of the floor.
Surprisingly, neither of these were what led to her
unfortunate and premature demise. Instead, it was the
balcony on the third floor of this mansion. She was
climbing on the railing — as she often did — in order to
better enjoy the view of the sunset, when she fell to
her death. But then something strange happened: she
got back up and continued with her wacky antics.
Her parents moved out shortly after, because the
place reminded them of Abby. She was the first of us
supernatural things to come to this mansion. It's weird,
she hasn't realized she's dead, even though she can fly
and disappear at will. Nowadays, she enjoys playing
pranks on all of us as much as she can.
Abby
The troublemaker
Age: 30 (died age 4)
Species: Ghost
Alignment: Good
